{
  "question_id": "01d1ddd2-8e2a-44ff-b510-e8c7b8cf8560",
  "short_text": "Inverted Pyramid",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print an **Inverted Pyramid** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n*****\r\n ***\r\n  *\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as an **Inverted Pyramid** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\r\n\r\n- The stars (`*`) should be printed on **4** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-inverted-pyramid.png' widthPercent='70'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates one space (\" \").\r\n- The Star in the box indicates a star  (\"*\").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n*******\r\n *****\r\n  ***\r\n   *\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "5b211030-f4e2-44b1-8cea-eea6761d0bad",
      "code_content": "number_of_rows = int(input())\n\nfor row in range(number_of_rows):\n    spaces = \" \" * row\n    stars = \"*\" * (2 * (number_of_rows - row) - 1)\n    \n    each_row = spaces + stars\n    \n    print(each_row)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
